article.headline: Idaho St. 69, N. Arizona 67
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Demetrius Monroe scored off an offensive rebound with 7.5 seconds left, helping Idaho State overcome an 11-point second-half deficit and defeat Northern Arizona 69-67 on Sunday. Amorrow Morgan scored 21 points and Matt Stucki, whose missed shot with 11 seconds left set up Monroe's game-winner, had 10. Monroe finished with eight. Stucki also took a charge with 0.9 seconds left to preserve the win for the Bengals (8-12, 5-2 Big Sky), who overcame three technical fouls and the ejection of coach Joe O'Brien. Kyle Landry scored a career-high 30 points to lead Northern Arizona (14-7, 6-2). Nathan Geiser added 10.
